# ERP Workspace Save-and-Close Standard

## Phase

ERP GLOBAL UI.FIX.1 — Save-and-Close Dirty Dialog Race Condition Fix (2026-06-19)

---

## Rule 1 — Always use `forceCloseActiveTab` after a successful save

After a successful save in a workspace form, **never** call `handleRequestClose()` or `closeTab(activeTab.id)` directly.
Instead, always call `forceCloseActiveTab()`.

### Why

`resetDirty()` schedules a React state update (async). When `closeTab()` runs immediately after in the same async tick,
the workspace store still sees `dirty: true` and shows the "Unsaved changes in this tab" confirmation dialog — even
though data was just saved. `forceCloseActiveTab()` bypasses this race condition because the data is already persisted.

### Correct pattern

```tsx
const { closeTab, activeTab, forceCloseActiveTab } = useWorkspace();

// Cancel / X button — uses handleRequestClose (dirty guard applies)
const handleRequestClose = () => closeTab(activeTab?.id ?? "");

// Save & Close — always use forceCloseActiveTab
const handleSaveAndClose = async () => {
  const ok = await handleSave();
  if (ok) forceCloseActiveTab(); // ← correct: bypasses stale dirty flag
};
```

### Forbidden pattern

```tsx
// ❌ NEVER — shows spurious "Unsaved changes" dialog after save
const handleSaveAndClose = async () => {
  const ok = await handleSave();
  if (ok) handleRequestClose();      // ← wrong
  if (ok) closeTab(activeTab.id);    // ← wrong
};

// ❌ NEVER — markDirty hack doesn't work due to React 18 batching
if (success) {
  markDirty(activeTab.id, false);    // ← batched, doesn't update before closeTab reads state
  closeTab(activeTab?.id ?? "");     // ← still sees old dirty=true
}
```

### `{ force: true }` equivalence

`forceCloseActiveTab()` is equivalent to `closeTab(activeTab.id, { force: true })`.
You may also use the explicit form in special cases where the active tab is not the target.

