## Rule 2 — Never nest `<Button>` inside `<DropdownMenuTrigger>`

This ERP uses **Base UI** (`@base-ui/react/menu`), not Radix UI.
`DropdownMenuTrigger` from `src/components/ui/dropdown-menu.tsx` renders its own `<button>` element and does NOT support `asChild`.

Placing a `<Button>` component inside `<DropdownMenuTrigger>` creates a `<button><button>` nesting which is invalid HTML and causes a hydration error.

### Correct pattern — style `DropdownMenuTrigger` directly

```tsx
<DropdownMenuTrigger className="inline-flex h-8 w-8 items-center justify-center rounded-md hover:bg-accent hover:text-accent-foreground">
  <span className="sr-only">Open menu</span>
  <MoreHorizontal className="h-4 w-4" />
</DropdownMenuTrigger>
```

### Forbidden patterns

```tsx
// ❌ NEVER — nested button, hydration error
<DropdownMenuTrigger>
  <Button variant="ghost" size="sm">
    <MoreVertical className="h-4 w-4" />
  </Button>
</DropdownMenuTrigger>

// ❌ NEVER — asChild does not exist on Base UI Menu.Trigger
<DropdownMenuTrigger asChild>
  <Button>...</Button>
</DropdownMenuTrigger>
```

---

## Rule 3 — `handleRequestClose` is for cancel/X only

`handleRequestClose` (which calls `closeTab` without `force`) must only be used for cancel/close buttons where
the dirty-state dialog should appear if the form has unsaved changes.

```tsx
// ✓ Cancel button — dirty dialog appears if form is dirty
<Button variant="outline" onClick={handleRequestClose}>Cancel</Button>

// ✓ X / close icon — dirty dialog appears if form is dirty
<button onClick={handleRequestClose}><X /></button>
```

It must never be called from a save-success path.
